f=Executive Office/marcus/custom/okr-cascade/SKILL.md · in=okr-cascade takes company- venture-level vision/priority statement turns quarterly Objectives Key Results cascade cleanly down departments teams, without cascade itself becoming game telephone. built merging two marketplace sources: `brainstorm-okrs`'s generation mechanics (produce multiple credible OKR options, grounded OKR/KPI/NSM theory) `setting-okrs-goals`'s coaching discipline (74 insights product leaders what makes OKRs fail vague objectives, tasks disguised key results, goals set before strategy, cascades drift company goal). · p=Give marcus (or whoever marcus advising) repeatable way "here's our priority quarter" small set inspiring, measurable objectives top level, defensible, aligned objectives department/team level below while catching common failure modes before they ship org. · wu=Triggers: "set OKRs," "quarterly planning," "cascade objectives," "what [team]'s goals quarter," any time top-level priority needs translated department- team-level commitments. · st:/ Protocol=`Confirm strategy exists (not goals-before-strategy) \· -> Gather context (level, stage, existing vs. fresh goals) \· -> Draft top-level objective(s) + key results \· -> Cascade: for each department/team, draft objectives that ladder up \· -> Check each draft against the pitfall checklist` · h3:Phase Confirm Strategy Exists=Before drafting any objective, confirm operator actual strategy diagnosis guiding policy see `strategy-advisor` `decision-critic` skills already assigned marcus). there's real strategy yet, say directly stop: OKRs written before strategy become false-precision exercises. draft goals fill gap. · h3:Phase Gather Context=Ask (or read provided documents): · h3:Phase Gather Context=What level company, venture/department, team, individual?, Company/venture stage (early, scaling, mature) changes what's ambitious vs. reckless., fresh goals revision existing ones?, What immediately-above level's goal, level's objective ladder directly? · h3:Phase Draft Top-Level Objective(s) Key Results=Cap top level **no three company/venture goals** dilutes focus prevents real trade-offs. objective: · h3:Phase Draft Top-Level Objective(s) Key Results=**Objective**: qualitative, inspirational, time-bound (typically quarterly). make reader want get out bed, read like generic corporate language., **Key Results**: exactly possible, triangulated one hardcore quantitative number, one squishier quality measure, one dollar sign. Prefer absolute numbers over ratios/percentages (ratios gamed shrinking denominator). · h3:Phase Draft Top-Level Objective(s) Key Results=Generate **2-3 alternative credible sets**, single "right" answer present them equal weight operator choose blend, `brainstorm-okrs`'s approach. Flag any assumptions about data availability. · h3:Phase 4 — Cascade=department/team below top level, draft objective that: · h3:Phase 4 — Cascade=Stays **no one step away** level above don't let get cascaded oblivion through multiple translation layers., Ladders explicitly: state one sentence team's objective moves company/venture-level key result., owned exactly one accountable owner. · h3:Phase 4 — Cascade=Repeat Phase 3's key-result discipline KRs, triangulated, absolute numbers) level. · h3:Phase Pitfall Check=Before presenting any draft, check objective/KR set against list flag violations rather silently fixing them (the operator see what wrong): · h3:Phase Pitfall Check=**Key results really tasks** ("launch features") instead measurable outcomes., **Too many goals** any one level (cap: 3)., **Vague objectives** using generic corporate language instead real, specific goal., **Goals set before strategy** (see Phase 1)., **Over-indexing single metric** gamed expense user/customer., **Ratios/percentages key results** absolute number harder game. · h3:Phase 6 — Present=`## OKR Cascade: [scope/quarter] \·  \· ### Top-Level Objective(s) — [2-3 alternative sets] \· [Objective, 3 Key Results, brief rationale, per set] \· ` · h3:Phase 6 — Present=Save substantial output markdown document (e.g. `OKRs-[scope]-[quarter].md`) requested. · pr=**Strategy first, goals second.** Never invent strategy justify OKRs., **One step goal above.** Cascading through many layers dilutes distorts intent keep short., **Systems over one-time targets.** possible, favor goals build recurring, "default-on" system rather single quarter's target., **Outcomes, outputs.** Success problem solved, feature shipped., **Separate strategy conversations OKR conversations.** Don't let "what do" "how measure it" blur together., **Planning overhead cap.** Planning consume roughly 10% execution period it's planning for., **No manufactured certainty.** data validate key result doesn't exist yet, say don't fabricate target. · f=strategy exists yet, stop Phase route operator `strategy-advisor` `decision-critic` first., operator wants one level (e.g. top-level objectives, cascade), Phases 1-3 5-6 don't force cascade wasn't asked for., department/team-level context missing (don't know who owns what), ask rather assume owner., asked deeper grounding any single principle, full 74-insight reference set available setting-okrs-goals source (`references/guest-insights.md`) pull specific insights request rather dumping whole file default. · b:with Other marcus Skills=okr-cascade produces objectives; `decision-critic` stress-test any objective key result operator unsure about before it's finalized., okr-cascade venture/initiative resource-allocation scoring that's `venture-priority-matrix`., Vision articulation (`vision-exploration`) upstream skill okr-cascade assumes vision/direction already exists cascade from.